The paper focuses on deep neural network-based image reconstruction for computed tomography, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of trainable convolutional neural networks (CNN) and deep UNet, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of iterative algorithms and data fidelity, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
